Responsible Social Media Use: Checklist for College Students
 Do’s
Think before posting – Make sure your content is appropriate and respectful.
Protect your privacy – Use strong passwords and adjust privacy settings.
Verify information before sharing – Avoid spreading fake news or rumors.
Maintain a positive digital footprint – Share content that reflects your values and goals.
Respect others online – Be polite and avoid offensive or harmful comments.

 Don’ts
Don’t share personal information publicly – Avoid posting your address, phone number, or passwords.
Don’t engage in cyberbullying – Never post or support harmful content about others.
Don’t overshare – Keep some aspects of your life private.
Don’t post in anger or frustration – Emotional posts can lead to regret later.
Don’t trust everything you see online – Be cautious of scams, misinformation, and fake accounts.
